HEADWORD: Text-hand
<hw>Text"-hand`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A large hand in writing; -- so called because it was
the practice to write the text of a book in a large hand and the notes
in a smaller hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Textile</ent>⟦br⟧
